attachments.title: Pok Pok’s Andy Ricker Closing Sen Yai; Nate Tilden of Olympia Provisions to Open Honky Tonk Taco in Its SE Division Space
attachments.text: Ricker will consolidate territory and expands his Whiskey Soda Lounge, while Tilden adds another charm to his fast-casual food bracelet.
attachments.fallback: Portland Monthly: Pok Pok’s Andy Ricker Closing Sen Yai; Nate Tilden of Olympia Provisions to Open Honky Tonk Taco in Its SE Division Space

text: I never liked the idea of that place
I’m not paying $10 for you to give me pre-packaged ramen
i wanted to love sen yai more than i actually did
i’d go every few months and it was… ok.
I live four blocks away for a month then am moving so I hope it burns

i think its reliably yummy and never too crowded. My mind has never been blown but it’s my go to spot when i have a noodle craving, and they have the little thai condiment cart that I wish every thai restaurant had.
